comments: Hall (OKC) and Noah (LAC) engage and disengage with one another as Noah rolls toward the post.
Hall (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as contact occurs with Noah (LAC) at the end of the drive.
Roberson (OKC) jumps toward McGruder (LAC) after the release of his shot attempt and makes marginal contact that does not affect McGruder's follow-through.
Hervey (OKC) makes slight contact with McGruder's (LAC) backside during his upward shooting motion.
Mann (LAC) makes contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it from Roberson (OKC) during rebounding.
Hall (OKC) makes incidental body/arm contact with Mann's (LAC) front during rebounding.
Noah (LAC) legally contests Diallo's (OKC) put-back attempt; any "high-five" contact is deemed incidental.
Patterson (LAC) rests his left hand on Diallo's (OKC) body as marginal contact occurs during rebounding and the put-back attempt.
Correctly called Delay of Game warning on OKC.
Roberson (OKC) briefly has his arms around Noah's (LAC) upper half before correcting.
Noah (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Roberson's (OKC) path and does not deliver the contact.
Hervey (OKC) swipes down and makes legal hand-on-ball contact with of Mann (LAC) at the end of the drive.
After having the ball partially dislodged, Mann (LAC) re-gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two legal steps before starting his upward shooting motion.
Hervey (OKC) turns and initiates contact with Mann's (LAC) side/arm during his upward shooting motion.
Roberson (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Coffey's (LAC) path and gives Coffey room to avoid the contact.
After the expiration of the pick, Coffey (LAC) and Roberson (OKC) engage and disengage with one another as they roll toward the lane.
Noah (LAC) fully extends both of his hands forward and initiates contact with Burton's (OKC) front that affects his driving shot attempt.
Roberson (OKC) and Noah (LAC) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Noah (LAC) and Roberson (OKC) make incidental arm contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Noah (LAC) legally contests Diallo's (OKC) jump shot attempt; any ensuing "high-five" contact is deemed incidental.
Patterson (LAC) makes contact with Roberson's (OKC) arm that affects his ability to rebound.
McGruder (LAC) makes incidental contact with Roberson (OKC) and Burton (OKC) as he cleanly pokes the ball free during rebounding.
Noah (LAC) jumps vertically as Diallo (OKC) drives toward him and makes incidental contact with his arm after his release on the driving shot attempt.
Hall (OKC) is moving alongside Noah's (LAC) path and absorbs that contact that occurs as Noah drives into the lane. Hall then makes clean contact the ball as Noah attempts to pass.
Roberson (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Coffey's (LAC) path and gives Coffey room to avoid the contact.
Coffey (LAC) commits the take foul on Hall (OKC).
Mann (LAC) places his off-arm on Bazley's (OKC) front at the end of the drive and quickly releases without extending it into Bazley.
Mann (LAC) places both hands against Bazley's (OKC) front at the start of the drive.
Mann (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it from Hervey (OKC) after he picks up his dribble.
After the initial clean dislodge, Mann (LAC) makes hand-on-ball contact to dislodge the ball again from Hervey (OKC).
Noah (LAC) moves toward the loose ball as marginal contact occurs with Bazley (OKC) during the rebound.
McGruder (LAC) rests his forearm on Burton's (OKC) front as marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Noah (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Diallo's (OKC) path and extends his left arm forward as he braces for the contact, which he absorbs.
Diallo (OKC) commits the take foul on Mann (LAC).
Bazley (OKC) legally contests Patterson's (LAC) jump shot attempt and cleanly blocks it.
Diallo (OKC) attempts to commit the take foul on Mann (LAC), but the contact is marginal.
Diallo (OKC) commits the take foul on Mann (LAC).
Noah (LAC) and Bazley (OKC) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Patterson (LAC) rests his forearm on Burton's (OKC) backside as marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Patterson (LAC) cleanly dislodges Bazley (OKC) of the ball before incidental arm contact is made thereafter during the rebound.
Hervey (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Coffey's (LAC) path and allows Coffey to move around the screen after initial contact takes place.
Hall (OKC) commits the take foul on Coffey (LAC).
McGruder (LAC) and Hall (OKC) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Hall (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Patterson's (LAC) path and does not deliver the contact.

Coffey (LAC) initiates contact across Hall's (OKC) front and makes foot-to-foot contact with Hall. The contact occurs as Hall retrieves the rebound and prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.
Patterson (LAC) makes marginal contact with Diallo's (OKC) front during rebounding.
Mann (LAC) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Patterson (LAC) rests his hand against Bazley's (OKC) backside and quickly releases as the inbound pass is made.
Diallo (OKC) commits the take foul on Patterson (LAC).
